## Docs: Update lifecycle/status-gate documentation

### Context
The middleware fix that narrowed `_STATUS_GATE_EDIT_PATHS` from the broad
`/dtwin/sync/` prefix to explicit `/dtwin/sync/start` and `/dtwin/sync/load`
entries was not reflected in the user-facing documentation. Three files
described the edit gate in ways that implied the entire Build/sync surface
(including Explorer queries) was locked on non-DRAFT versions.

### Changes

1. `docs/user-guide.md`
   ÔÇö Lifecycle section: clarified that only Build (`/dtwin/sync/start`) and
     Load (`/dtwin/sync/load`) are blocked when not DRAFT; read-only KG
     operations (Explorer filter, stats, status) remain accessible.

2. `docs/architecture.md`
   ÔÇö "Version lifecycle & API access" callout: expanded the one-liner about
     the DRAFT edit gate to enumerate what is blocked vs. what stays open.

3. `docs/api.md`
   ÔÇö Knowledge Graph Endpoints: replaced the single `GET /dtwin/sync/status`
     stub with four documented endpoints (`POST /dtwin/sync/start`,
     `POST /dtwin/sync/load`, `POST /dtwin/sync/filter`,
     `GET /dtwin/sync/status`) plus a status-gate warning box on start/load.

### Modified files
- `docs/user-guide.md`
- `docs/architecture.md`
- `docs/api.md`

### Test results
- `uv run pytest -q --tb=no` Ôćĺ 2998 passed, 58 pre-existing failures (unrelated to this change ÔÇö same count with and without these edits), 17 skipped

