## Docs: July 2026 Roadmap (Roadmap_2026-07.md)

### Context
v0.6.0 shipped several features but deferred five items to a future release
(ontology iteration UX, mapping multi-select, mapping orphan detection,
scheduled reasoning, temporal & recursive Datalog). The July roadmap
captures the updated plan: those deferred items move to **v0.8.0**, whose
theme shifts from Enterprise Hardening to **Unstructured Data & Workflow
Completeness**. The previous v0.8.0 Enterprise Hardening scope moves to
**v0.9.0**; v1.0.0 GA shifts to Q1 2027.

### Changes

1. `releases/Roadmap_2026-07.md` (new file)
   - Executive summary updated with four strategic axes (Neo4j, unstructured data, workflow completeness, enterprise hardening).
   - v0.6.0 section reflects actual deliveries and marks five items as `Ôć¬ Moved to v0.8.0`.
   - v0.7.0 Neo4j Connector unchanged (August 2026).
   - v0.8.0 rewritten: two pillars ÔÇö unstructured data ingestion pipeline (7 capabilities) + deferred workflow items from v0.6.0 (5 capabilities); target October 2026.
   - v0.9.0 new section: former v0.8.0 Enterprise Hardening + triple store migration UX; target Q4 2026.
   - v1.0.0 GA shifted to Q1 2027.
   - Feature matrix updated to reflect all version changes.
   - Open Questions updated with two new unstructured-data questions.

### Modified files
- `releases/Roadmap_2026-07.md` (created)

### Test results
- No code changes ÔÇö documentation only.

