## Security: Batch dependency security-patch (24 advisories)

### Context
GitHub Dependabot raised 24 security alerts (High/Moderate/Low) across the
main `uv.lock` and `src/mcp-server/uv.lock` lock files. All affected packages
had patched versions available. This change bumps version floors in
`pyproject.toml` (direct deps + `[tool.uv] constraint-dependencies`) and
regenerates the lock file so every resolved package is on a patched release.

One advisory (NLTK path traversal, GHSA-p4gq-832x-fm9v / CVE-2026-54293) is
tracked as a TODO comment in the pitfalls optional dep because the fix ships in
`nltk>=3.10.0` which is only available as `3.10.0-rc1` at this time.
Mitigation: never pass user-controlled input to `nltk.data.load()`.

### Changes

1. `pyproject.toml`
   - `pydantic-settings`: `>=2.1.0` Ôćĺ `>=2.14.2`
     (GHSA-4xgf-cpjx-pc3j ÔÇö NestedSecretsSettingsSource symlink traversal)
   - `python-multipart`: `>=0.0.27` Ôćĺ `>=0.0.30`
     (GHSA-5rvq-cxj2-64vf / CVE-2026-53539 ÔÇö quadratic ';'-sep parsing DoS;
      semicolon parameter smuggling; RFC 2231 Content-Disposition smuggling;
      negative Content-Length unbounded memory buffer)
   - `starlette`: `>=1.0.1` Ôćĺ `>=1.3.1`
     (GHSA-82w8-qh3p-5jfq / CVE-2026-54283 ÔÇö request.form() limits ignored for
      urlencoded bodies; GHSA-86qp-5c8j-p5mr ÔÇö BadHost hostname poisoning)
   - `nltk` (pitfalls extra): `>=3.8.0` Ôćĺ `>=3.9.4` with TODO comment
     (GHSA-p4gq-832x-fm9v / CVE-2026-54293 ÔÇö URL-encoded path traversal,
      fix pending stable release of nltk 3.10.0)
   - Constraint `aiohttp`: `>=3.14.0` Ôćĺ `>=3.14.1`
     (GHSA-xcgm-r5h9-7989 / CVE-2026-54274 ÔÇö incomplete WS frame mem bypass;
      GHSA-63hw-fmq6-xxg2 / CVE-2026-54277 ÔÇö C parser max_line_size bypass;
      GHSA-4fvr-rgm6-gqmc / CVE-2026-54273 ÔÇö pipelined requests queue DoS;
      + 5 more Low/Moderate aiohttp issues all fixed in 3.14.1)
   - New constraint `pyjwt>=2.13.0`
     (GHSA-xgmm-8j9v-c9wx / CVE-2026-48526 ÔÇö JWK accepted as HMAC secret;
      GHSA-jq35-7prp-9v3f ÔÇö alg allow-list bypass via PyJWK/PyJWKClient;
      + SSRF via scheme allowlist; unbounded Base64URL DoS; JWKS kid DoS)
   - New constraint `msgpack>=1.2.1`
     (GHSA-6v7p-g79w-8964 ÔÇö Unpacker out-of-bounds read / crash on reuse)
   - New constraint `cryptography>=48.0.1`
     (GHSA-537c-gmf6-5ccf / CVE-2026-34180 ÔÇö vulnerable OpenSSL in PyPI wheels)

2. `uv.lock` (regenerated)
   - aiohttp           3.14.0 Ôćĺ 3.14.1
   - cryptography      46.0.7 Ôćĺ 48.0.1
   - mlflow* trio      3.11.1 Ôćĺ 3.14.0  (pulled in by dep-graph updates)
   - msgpack           1.1.2  Ôćĺ 1.2.1
   - pydantic-settings 2.12.0 Ôćĺ 2.14.2
   - pyjwt             2.12.1 Ôćĺ 2.13.0
   - python-multipart  0.0.27 Ôćĺ 0.0.32
   - starlette         1.2.1  Ôćĺ 1.3.1

### Modified files
- `pyproject.toml`
- `uv.lock`

